  "support": "Fragment of grey-white marble with blue-grey veining. The right edge appears intact, broken on the other three sides. The rear of the piece preserves a double moulding along the lower edge, which is not perpendicular to the text on the obverse. The clear implication is that the stone is a piece of marble veneer that has been subsequently re-used for the inscription.",
